'''Argie bargie''' or ''argy bargy'', pronounced "R G bar G" is a [[United Kingdom|British]] slang term meaning to argue contentiously. It gained notoriety during the [[Falklands war]] in a newspaper headline to describe the actions of the [[Argentine]]s (so-called "argies"). The origin of the term is from Scottish.

